I decided to put pressure on d4 first before making any exchanges. There is possibility I may be able to draw the Queen away from the defense of the pawn by Bxb3 and also a possibility of Bxd2 drawing the Knight away from the defense winning me a central pawn. 

I have found that the timing of exchanges is often very important. If you can postpone an exchange while creating threats, it is often beneficial to do so.
